description: Chris Hans  is with  Ty-Munchie Dotson  and  26 others  at  The Irish P≈çl . I have things I need to say...  The Irish Pol has closed  First off, I would like to express how proud I am of what we were able to accomplish in a year at The Irish Pol. I'm proud of the The 100's of man hours it took to transform it into the bar/music venue it was. Also the family of regulars we both lovingly inherited and accumulated while we were there. All of you will be missed.  The Irish Pol staff, event promoters, and people who helped us that are tagged in this post were not only a family but a group of people who made a difference. We brought business into that bar... a lot of it... We had a lot more coming. Be proud of that. Anyone looking for Bartenders or cooks please look no further then the people tagged here. They are some of the best in the city and will only help your bar. I will miss all the daily laughs and endless hours of fun we had.  Big thanks to  John Pickles  for having our backs. Also for helping me with insane, overnight construction and painting projects that no one ever noticed. "I don't know why but I feel more comfortable in here." Was the best compliment we ever got from our customers. Couldn't have done any of this without you dude.  Also big thanks to  Mike Hans . Getting to work with my brother on a project made this last year awesome. Also keep checking back for what we do next.  In conclusion, I am thankful to have had the opportunity at all. Without it I would have never been able to meet all the wonderful people I did over the last year. Once I get back on my feet I will be occupying a bar stool again in Olde City very soon to visit you all. Mike Hans Chris Hans Chris Hans
